The cloud-based data warehousing company, which enables enterprises to store, manage and analyze massive datasets across multiple cloud providers, said demand for its platform is accelerating.

headline: Even Nvidia Has Speed Limits

After a moment of panic earlier this year as President Trump kicked off his trade war, Nvidia has come roaring back.  By Wednesday’s close, the stock was up 65% since Trump’s “Liberation Day” event on April 2, compared with average gains of 27% for  Microsoft Amazon.com Meta Platforms  and Google’s parent,  Alphabet  Those happen to be the companies spending the most in snapping up Nvidia’s chips to build their own AI services.
